fixes: Fix in parsing plugin configs for access_control
Bugfix in pagination logic in case of active screenshare/plugins
Bugfix in permission checks for localUser.enableAudio() and localUser.enableVideo()
Bugfix in localUser.disableScreenshare() for a check if screenshare is already in progress.
Bugfix in disabling camera track if user toggles video in setup screen before joining the meeting
Bugfix in kick and kick-all api's for meetings

new_api: Added PluginConfig in DytePlugin to read the value of accessControl set on the Dyte Developer Portal

fixes: Bugfix in disposing camera and audio track in case of waiting room entry rejected.
Bugfix in VideoView cache in the core sdk when useCache is disabled.
Bugfix in media for corrupt frames on selected android devices
Bugfix in onPin/onUnpin events in DyteParticipantUpdateListeners
Bugfix in waiting rooms for V1 meetings for parsing WaitingRoomType
Bugfix in emitting onActiveParticipantsChanged event in case of empty page
Bugfix in emitting onParticipantChanged event
Bugfix in emitting onActiveSpeakerChanged and onNoActiveSpeaker
Performance improvements in the media layer of the SDK
Bugfix in emitting onMeetingInitFailed event in case of a waiting room flow
Bugfix in destroying the video views created inside the core SDK
Bugfix in DyteStage where sometimes duplicate stage requests were shown in accessRequests
Fixed emitting redudent events for `onActiveParticipantsChanged()` inside DyteParticipantEventsListener

new_api: Added a callbacks in Plugins to listen to arbirary messages shared on plugin webviews.
Added an api in DytePlugin to send arbitary data to Plugin webviews.
fixes: Fixed an issue on local user for disabling audio/video tracks once local user leaves the stage in webinar calls.
Improved kick and kick-all api's in the core SDK
Fixed an issue in emitting public events from the core SDK where sometimes events were not getting triggered for all attached listeners.
Fixed an issue with DyteStage where we create audio/video tracks for only on-stage users.

new_api: DyteRecording class now have [pause()](../android-core/recording) and [resume()](../android-core/recording) methods to pause a recording and resume the same recording
fixes: Fixed an issue with DyteStage where the stage status was not updating correctly when a participant received a request to join stage
Fixed an issue where callback was not getting triggered on un-pinning a participant
Fixed a crash for customers targeting Android 14 as their compileSdk configuration on their application
